    ],
    "retry_config": "No retry mechanism mentioned. A single transient Onfido failure (network blip, 500) immediately fails the user's registration. At minimum, 1 retry with jitter on 5xx/timeout is a must-have.",
    "timeout_config": "5s timeout is set. This is reasonable given Onfido's p99 of 3s, but without a circuit breaker the timeout only protects individual requests — it does not protect the system from sustained degradation.",
    "circuit_breakers": "None. This is the critical gap. Without a circuit breaker, every request during an Onfido outage will block for 5s then fail, consuming resources and providing a terrible user experience for the full duration of the outage.",
    "graceful_degradation": "None. The service has exactly two modes: fully working or fully broken. There is no provisional/pending KYC state that would allow users to register and complete verification later."
  },

  "operational_readiness": {
