    "on_call_documentation": "Not mentioned. On-call engineer needs a runbook covering: (1) what to do when Onfido is down, (2) how to manually unblock users stuck in KYC, (3) escalation contacts at Onfido, (4) how to toggle KYC enforcement if needed.",
    "new_infrastructure_required": {
      "new_env_vars": [],
      "new_services": [],
      "new_queues_topics": [
        "If async KYC fallback is implemented: a durable queue (e.g., SQS/Kafka topic) for deferred KYC checks"
      ],
      "config_changes": [
        "Circuit breaker configuration (failure threshold, recovery timeout, half-open limits)",
        "Retry policy configuration (max retries, backoff multiplier, jitter)"
      ],
      "infra_provisioning": []
    },
    "database_safety": {
      "has_migrations": false,
      "reversible": true,
      "data_preserving": true,
      "large_table_impact": false,
      "details": "No database migrations mentioned. If a provisional KYC state is added, a schema change to the user/registration table would be needed to track verification status."
    },
    "verdict": "NOT READY"
  },

  "escalations": [
    {
      "type": "integration_risk",
      "issue": "Onfido SLA (99.9%) is lower than the internal SLA target (99.95%), and the architecture provides zero decoupling — the service's availability is strictly bounded by Onfido's availability",
      "reason": "It is mathematically impossible to meet 99.95% uptime when a synchronous, non-bypassable dependency guarantees at most 99.9%. This is not a nice-to-have fix — it is an architectural constraint that requires either (a) async/deferred KYC with provisional registration, or (b) lowering the internal SLA target. This decision has blast radius beyond this service (affects onboarding flows, downstream transaction eligibility, compliance workflows) and needs architectural guidance.",
      "routed_to": "MJ"
    },
    {
      "type": "integration_risk",
      "issue": "No circuit breaker, no retry, no fallback — single external dependency failure causes total registration outage",
      "reason": "The absence of any resilience pattern (circuit breaker, retry, fallback, bulkhead) on a critical-path external API call means the blast radius of an Onfido outage is unbounded: all registrations fail, thread pools may exhaust under sustained timeouts, and there is no automatic recovery. The on-call engineer's only option is to wait for Onfido to recover or deploy a code change. MJ should define the target architecture for graceful degradation.",
      "routed_to": "MJ"
    }
  ],

  "confidence": {
    "level": 55,
